, and the feedback to health care. As an economist, she is concerned with the efficiency or cost-effectiveness of the system from the point of view of its three social purposes: deterrence of medical negligence, compensation of injured patients, and the spreading of risk. To provide evidence of the operation of the system in practice, to distinguish fact from allegation, and to evaluate proposals for reform, she has undertaken a detailed empirical analysis of malpractice claims and insurance markets. It is a major contribution to our understanding of how the system works in practice and how it might be improved.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAansprakelijkheid. 0aArtsen. 0aÄrztlicher Kunstfehler. 0aFouten. 0aSoziale Probleme, Sozialdienste, Versicherungen. 0aÄrztlicher Kunstfehler. 4aMEDICAL / General. 4aMalpractice insurance -- United States. 4aMedical personnel -- Malpractice -- Economic aspects -- United States. 4aPhysicians -- Malpractice -- Economic aspects -- United States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Law & Political Science eBook Packagez9783110353495oZDB-23-HLP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067433113640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067433114340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674331143423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674331143.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA